HEADWORD: Pteridophyta
<hw>Pter`i*doph"y*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <?/, <?/, a fern + <?/ a plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
class of flowerless plants, embracing ferns, horsetails, club mosses,
quillworts, and other like plants. See the Note under
<er>Cryptogamia</er>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pter"i*do*phyte`</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This is a modern term, devised to replace the older ones
<xex>acrogens</xex> and <xex>vascular Cryptogamia</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pterobranchia</ent>⟦br⟧
